thread.title: Canberra Convention Bureau names new chief

author: eTN Global Editor
title: Canberra Convention Bureau names new chief
text:
Canberra Convention Bureau names new chief Adv: Canberra Convention Bureau has announced that Michael Matthews is its new Chief Executive Officer Adv: 
CANBERRA, Australia - Canberra Convention Bureau has announced that Michael Matthews is its new Chief Executive Officer, commencing 1 October 2015. 
Originally from Australia, Mr Matthews has spent the past 14 years in roles encompassing sales, operations and destination marketing in the Canadian market and is currently the Executive Director of Meetings and Conventions PEI, which is responsible for marketing, sales and product development for the province of Prince Edward Island in Canada.
